parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to vibrate or shake violently, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates violently
especially when turning
backing up
or driving at low speeds. The power steering warning light may illuminate on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel locks or becomes stuck
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel locks or becomes stuck
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS brake light comes on
the brakes feel soft or squishy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes may not engage immediately
the vehicle may lurch forward or feel like it's speeding up when braking
and the brake pedal may go to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic behavior of the brake pedal can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to stop or takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake system fails to engage
the brakes do not work properly
the brake pedal goes to the floor
and the vehicle takes longer to stop or does not stop at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the vehicle loses power
the warning lights illuminate
the vehicle can only operate on electric mode
the air conditioner blows hot air
and the vehicle may not restart immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of oil in the intake manifold can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: Oil in the intake manifold
engine stalling
loss of power
warning lights illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Grinding noise when braking and accelerating
transmission needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a thermostat gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of overheating issues, leading to potential engine damage and safety risks.
symptoms: No thermostat gauge
vehicle overheating
engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Hybrid system failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Warning lights illuminating
vehicle stalling
loss of power
hybrid system failure.
